@NODE "Mail.0" "Re[3]: Amiga Mode"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Tue, 02 Jun 1998 06:47:59 -0500
Subject: Re[3]: Amiga Mode

Hi Damir,

On 01-Jun-98, Damir Arh wrote:
> Hello Curt

>>> 4. I don't open any windows. But if I'll for any reason have to open a
>>>   borderless wholescreen window, what could I use instead of ShowBitMap
> to
>>>   achieve double buffering and prevent flickering?
> 
>> You can still use ShowBitmap - but of course, the game won't work on a GFX
>> card.
> 
> Yes, I realise that. But in the moment GFX card compatibility isn't one of
> my primary objectives.
> 
>> You could also use 2 windows - both full size, and one in front of the
> other. 
>> Then draw on the back one, put it in front, etc.
> 
> That would probably be okay for GFX cards to, but in this case I shouldn't
> use any blitting, right?

Well, you can use Wblit.  And also use a standard bitmap and use any bitmap
commands, then BitMapToWindow to put this on the window.

But this is not really a good method for either GFX card or standard system. 

The problem with this method is speed - I think this would slow down your
program a lot.  I'm not sure, I really haven't tried doing it this way.

Better to use ShowBitmap for standard systems.

And for GFX cards, use chunkies and Wpa8 or something.  I really don't know a
lot about GFX cards, I don't have one.
 
Later...
-- 
Ignorance is when you don't know
anything and somebody finds it out.

