On 30 Jun 98, at 23:31, Paul West tippy-tappy-typed:

> There's no stackpointer variable as you know. Macros are generally
> defined differently I think. Assembler in blitz statements may get
> fidgety if you try to use an rts (such as subroutine). Not sure if
> that can be worked around or not.
> 
> There may be other things to consider.

 If you intend on using ASM in statements or functions or want to mix ASM and blitz then 
you need to remember these things:

1) a3 is used as a pointer to strings when they are being manipulated
2) a4 is used as the local variable base (in statements / functions)
3) a5 is used as the global variable base


.oO_David_McMinn_Oo.


