I've only been able to do this by remaking the gadgetlist:

DetachGTList
Free GTLIST                  ;MUST do this!  Or else you get 2 or more copys!
(remake the entire GTlist)
AttachGTList

If you don't Free the GTlist before re-making it, intuition keeps BOTH copies,
and you can wind up with 2 (or more) sets of gadgets in the window at once. 
(and they all work, too!  I speak from experience - ie, I made this mistake
before!)

I haven't done this while the window is still open, but it should work for
that too.  You will probably need to do a WCLS to clear out the old gadget
images first, or at least do a Wbox over the gadget(s) you are changing.


The other part, about just adding a gadget - might work by just detaching the
GTlist, then re-attaching it.


