IFF is a fileformat standard, part of which is to support the storage
of ILBM pictures - InterLeaved BitMaps. The file has a number of
`chunks' which have a small header such as "CAMG" (amiga display
modes) or "BODY" bitmap data. There are chunks for colourcycling too.
If you could get hold of some saveiff sourcecode you could write a
little prog to save off the palette and colourcycling to an IFF file
with the appropriate chunks in it.

