Save you hair!  This works for me:

Ev.l=waitevent

if Ev=$20 or Ev=$40 then gh.w=GadgetHit

This way, gh will always hold the id number of the gadget that was hit.  Even
if other events happen later.

I think GadgetHit actually returns a Long, but unless you have over 32,000
gadgets a word should do  ;)

$20 is returned if a string gadget is clicked in, $40 when return is pressed
to end the input.  So use just one or the other (or both) depending on what
you are doing from there. 

