on as many systems as possible, because I discovered that those PPC
processors act quite differently. For example, marking memory as
noncachable in the voxelspace demo helped to improve the performance on
603E based systems a lot while it even slowed down the demo on 604E
based system (probably because of the much greater memory bandwidth).

Additionally I hope that those programmers will not only read the
technical part but also the rest about game play. I would rather buy a
game with a perfect game play, which is slower by 20 percent, than the
faster one, which is not playable at all. I think, that many programmers
spend too much time into performance and technical features. Therefore
I also hope, that standards like OpenGL will be supported by more and
more programmers in future (as soon as the performance will suffice
thanks to 3D hardware support) so that they can concentrate on other
features and they don't have to care for the lowlevel work anymore.

