From: Dave Newton <Dave@nbsamiga.demon.co.uk>
Date: Tue, 30 Jun 1998 13:47:34 -0000
Subject: New amiga games, and 25fps, and some blitting....


Hi all,

 Sorry about that. I was supposed to be going on holiday, and it's all been
canceled...so now I'm in a mess at the moment. Anyway, I just thought I'd
better email about a few things (sorry this isn't in any of the threads).

 Curt is completely correct about the 25fps thing. It's not the only way
to do it, but it's the best. My prefs program sets the fps by testing the
cpu (by just calling the maximum load of rouintes per frame, and working
out how many frames it will take). It will usually be on 25fps, and
if they have a incredibly fast machine, it may make 50fps...but I doubt
it. The slowdown in my game is the copy from the fastmem buffer to the
chipmem buffer...always seems to need nearly a frame to itself (320x256x8).
The way that Curt's works..if you haven't worked it out is too always force
a 25fps update, unless the routines take more than two frames...then it's
just as best as it can be. This is how a lot of pc games work. The point
is, say one update takes under a frame....and the next update takes over
a frame....just using a single vwait would make this very jerky, going
from 1 vwait to 2 vwait and so on, giving something like 33fps If I'm not
mistaken (didn't check...guessed). Where as, all the updates will take
2 frames giving you a more steady picture. 25fps will never look quite
as good as 50fps...but it is usable.

 I am still working on my blit routines. A clipblit is planned, and so
are some of the other features. I have finished the save/load for my
routines, but it's mostly untested. If you want to be a 'beta' tester
then email me, and I'll send you the latest version, so you can try it.
It'll be a week or so before there's more blitting stuff...but it will
