By crossfade do you mean that the pixels from the first picture are randomly
removed and replaced by the pixels in the second picture?

You can do this by using a point & plot method to read the pixels from the
second pic and send these to the first pic's bitmap.  You would want to set up
some sort of random table first to select which pixel is transferred.

