I and others were chatting about this on the blitz list the other day.
You might have to do a conversion to a HSV colourmodel instead of RGB
in order to properly fade the colours. The effect is essentially to do
a spread, a range of colours, for EVERY pixel, from the source colour
to the destination colour. Then, you'd need to devise a suitable
palette. Having the same palette in both pics would help.

If you can forego the 256-colour limit and have a situation where the
TOTAL number of bitplanes is no more than 8, there is a very simple
and quick palette fade you could use, but again generating the
inbetween colours is a bit tricky.

