First up, allocate sufficient memory in FastRAM to hold the IFF file you are
loading. The easiest way is to use Initbank to initialise a bank in FastRAM
(press HELP to see the number for FastRAM, I think it's 2) and use "BLoad"
to load the file into the beginning of the bank (adress found using Bank
command). The BLoad command is in the RIAmosFunc library, which is available
free from the RWE website or is part of B.S.Suite. Create a bitmap as normal
with all the correct width/height/bitplane values. Then use the "GrabILBM"
command (see above for availability) to grab the bitmap and palette. This
command also needs an adress input parameter, which is the "Bank" command
again.

eg. To load a bitmap into FastRAM (untested! warning...)

Initbank 1,Filesize("Test.IFF"),2
Bitmap 0,320,256,4
BLoad "Test.IFF",Bank(1)
GrabILBM 0,1,Bank(1) ; 2nd parameter is the destination palette

