> So this will produce a display that is in 25fps all the time with no
> jerkiness? What is this "tick" thing. Also, you don`t happen to have a
> little demo of this or know where there is an example of this?

Yes, this will always give a steady 25fps (30 fps in NTSC) unless your main
loop code is taking LONGER than 2 Vblanks to execute.  If that happens, you
will see a slowdown.

A Tick is simply 1 Vblank - ResetTimer sets the count to 0, then Ticks returns
the number of Vblanks that have passed since you reset.  So a "Tick" is 1/50
sec in PAL, or 1/60 in NTSC.

Sorry, I don't have any example for this - I did both my games to execute in
<1 vblank.  (They're simple...)

But just try inserting the code as shown and judge for yourself.

The code above simply checks how long your main loop took, and makes sure that
each frame takes at least 2 vblanks, regardless of processor speed or how many
objects you are handling at any time.  It is up to you to insure that your
code always completes the loop in less than 2 Vblanks.

The other suggestion is better, (inserting more graphics for faster machines,
etc.) - but this will get you started.

